{"title_page": "Jaswantnagar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Jaswantnagar\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = city\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| famous Drama             = Ramleela\n| famous food              = Murmuriya\n| pushpin_map             = India Uttar Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|26.88|N|78.9|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Etawah district|Etawah]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| leader_title1           = [[Jaswantnagar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|MLA (Jaswantnagar constituency)]]\n| leader_name1            = [[Shivpal Singh Yadav]] ([[Pragatisheel Samajwadi Party (Lohiya)]])\n| leader_title2           = [[Mainpuri (Lok Sabha constituency)|MP (Mainpuri constituency)]]\n| leader_name2            = [[Mulayam Singh Yadav]] ([[Samajwadi Party]])\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 133\n| population_total        = 28,164\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n\n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      =Languages \n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code   206245           = \n| registration_plate      = \n| website- jaswantnagar.gov.nic.in                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Jaswantnagar''' is a city and a [[municipal board]] in [[Etawah district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2011}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Jaswantnagar is a Nagar Palika Parishad city in district of Etawah, Uttar Pradesh. The Jaswantnagar city is divided into 25 wards for which elections are held every 5 years. The Jaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad has population of 28,164 of which 14,944 are males while 13,220 are females as per report released by Census India 2011.\n\nPopulation of Children with age of 0-6 is 3633 which is 12.90 % of total population of Jaswantnagar (NPP). In Jaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad, Female Sex Ratio is of 885 against state average of 912. Moreover Child Sex Ratio in Jaswantnagar is around 881 compared to Uttar Pradesh state average of 902. Literacy rate of Jaswantnagar city is 78.16 % higher than state average of 67.68 %. In Jaswantnagar, Male literacy is around 83.42 % while female literacy rate is 72.23 %.\n\nJaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad has total administration over 4,987 houses to which it supplies basic amenities like water and sewerage. It is also authorize to build roads within Nagar Palika Parishad limits and impose taxes on properties coming under its jurisdiction.it has big village dhanuan for 9 km from Jaswant nagar.\n\nJaswantnagar Religion Data 2011\nPopulation - 28164 ,\nHindu - 74.07% ,\nMuslim - 23.25% ,\nChristian - 0.04% ,\nSikh - 0.07% ,\nBuddhist - 0.09% ,\nJain - 2.42% ,\nOther - 0.00% ,\nNot stated - 0.06%\n\n\n.....\n\nWritten by '''Aman sharma (<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/amnshrma_/|title=Aman Sharma|last=|first=|date=|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>   Instagram )'''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Etawah district}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Etawah district]]\n\n\n{{Etawah-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Jaswantnagar\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = city\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| famous Drama             = Ramleela\n| famous food              = Murmuriya\n| pushpin_map             = India Uttar Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|26.88|N|78.9|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Etawah district|Etawah]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| leader_title1           = [[Jaswantnagar (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|MLA (Jaswantnagar constituency)]]\n| leader_name1            = [[Shivpal Singh Yadav]] ([[Pragatisheel Samajwadi Party (Lohiya)]])\n| leader_title2           = [[Mainpuri (Lok Sabha constituency)|MP (Mainpuri constituency)]]\n| leader_name2            = [[Mulayam Singh Yadav]] ([[Samajwadi Party]])\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 133\n| population_total        = 28,164\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n\n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      =Languages \n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code   206245           = \n| registration_plate      = \n| website- jaswantnagar.gov.nic.in                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Jaswantnagar''' is a city and a [[municipal board]] in [[Etawah district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{As of|2011}} India [[census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> Jaswantnagar is a Nagar Palika Parishad city in district of Etawah, Uttar Pradesh. The Jaswantnagar city is divided into 25 wards for which elections are held every 5 years. The Jaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad has population of 28,164 of which 14,944 are males while 13,220 are females as per report released by Census India 2011.\n\nPopulation of Children with age of 0-6 is 3633 which is 12.90 % of total population of Jaswantnagar (NPP). In Jaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad, Female Sex Ratio is of 885 against state average of 912. Moreover Child Sex Ratio in Jaswantnagar is around 881 compared to Uttar Pradesh state average of 902. Literacy rate of Jaswantnagar city is 78.16 % higher than state average of 67.68 %. In Jaswantnagar, Male literacy is around 83.42 % while female literacy rate is 72.23 %.\n\nJaswantnagar Nagar Palika Parishad has total administration over 4,987 houses to which it supplies basic amenities like water and sewerage. It is also authorize to build roads within Nagar Palika Parishad limits and impose taxes on properties coming under its jurisdiction.it has big village dhanuan for 9 km from Jaswant nagar.\n\nJaswantnagar Religion Data 2011\nPopulation - 28164 ,\nHindu - 74.07% ,\nMuslim - 23.25% ,\nChristian - 0.04% ,\nSikh - 0.07% ,\nBuddhist - 0.09% ,\nJain - 2.42% ,\nOther - 0.00% ,\nNot stated - 0.06%\n\n\n.....\n\nWritten by '''Aman sharma ('''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/amnshrma_/|title=Aman Sharma|last=|first=|date=|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Etawah district}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Etawah district]]\n\n\n{{Etawah-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Amnshrma", "label": "safe", "comment": "Add something about me", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jaswantnagar"}
